Most reference environments start from a common base:  a 32 - or 64 -bit Linux system built with Lubuntu ( http://lubuntu.net ), a lightweight variant of Ubuntu Linux.

The process of creating a reference environment to reprodu ce analysis is summarized in  Figure 2 and  described in detail in the Supplementary Information , as well as in the Guide to Reference Environments  online ( http://uomsystemsbiology.github.io/research/reference -environments/ ) .
